theorem Topology.P2_iUnion {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {ι : Sort*} {A : ι → Set X} :
    (∀ i, Topology.P2 (A i)) → Topology.P2 (⋃ i, A i) := by
  intro hA
  dsimp [Topology.P2] at hA ⊢
  intro x hx
  rcases Set.mem_iUnion.1 hx with ⟨i, hxi⟩
  have hxInt : x ∈ interior (closure (interior (A i))) := hA i hxi
  have hsubset :
      interior (closure (interior (A i))) ⊆
        interior (closure (interior (⋃ i, A i))) := by
    -- Step 1: `interior (A i) ⊆ interior (⋃ j, A j)`
    have h1 : interior (A i) ⊆ interior (⋃ j, A j) := by
      intro y hy
      exact Set.mem_iUnion.2 ⟨i, hy⟩
    -- Step 2: Take closures to obtain the corresponding inclusion
    have h2 : closure (interior (A i)) ⊆ closure (interior (⋃ j, A j)) :=
      closure_mono h1
    -- Step 3: Apply monotonicity of `interior`
    exact interior_mono h2
  exact hsubset hxInt

theorem Topology.P1_iUnion {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {ι : Sort*} {A : ι → Set X} :
    (∀ i, Topology.P1 (A i)) → Topology.P1 (⋃ i, A i) := by
  intro hA
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hA ⊢
  intro x hx
  rcases Set.mem_iUnion.1 hx with ⟨i, hxAi⟩
  have hx_closure : x ∈ closure (interior (A i)) := (hA i) hxAi
  have hsubset : closure (interior (A i)) ⊆ closure (interior (⋃ j, A j)) := by
    apply closure_mono
    have hsub_int : interior (A i) ⊆ interior (⋃ j, A j) := by
      apply interior_mono
      intro y hy
      have : (y : X) ∈ (A i) := (interior_subset : interior (A i) ⊆ (A i)) hy
      exact Set.mem_iUnion.2 ⟨i, this⟩
    exact hsub_int
  exact hsubset hx_closure

theorem interior_closure_interior_closure_eq_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    have hsubset : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
      have : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
      exact closure_mono this
    exact interior_mono hsubset
  ·
    have hsubset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
      intro x hx
      exact subset_closure hx
    exact interior_mono hsubset

theorem Topology.closure_interior_closure_interior_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure (interior A))) = closure (interior A) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    -- `interior (closure (interior A))` is contained in `closure (interior A)`
    have h₁ : interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
      intro x hx
      exact interior_subset hx
    -- Taking closures preserves inclusions
    have hclosure :
        closure (interior (closure (interior A))) ⊆
          closure (closure (interior A)) := closure_mono h₁
    simpa [closure_closure] using hclosure
  ·
    -- `interior A` is contained in `interior (closure (interior A))`
    have h₂ : interior A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
      apply interior_mono
      intro x hx
      exact subset_closure hx
    -- Taking closures preserves inclusions
    have hclosure :
        closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (interior A))) :=
      closure_mono h₂
    exact hclosure

theorem Topology.P2_iUnion {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {ι : Sort*} {A : ι → Set X} :
    (∀ i, Topology.P2 (A i)) → Topology.P2 (⋃ i, A i) := by
  intro hA
  dsimp [Topology.P2] at hA ⊢
  intro x hx
  rcases Set.mem_iUnion.1 hx with ⟨i, hxAi⟩
  have hxInt : x ∈ interior (closure (interior (A i))) := (hA i) hxAi
  have hsubset :
      interior (closure (interior (A i))) ⊆
        interior (closure (interior (⋃ j, A j))) := by
    apply interior_mono
    have : closure (interior (A i)) ⊆ closure (interior (⋃ j, A j)) := by
      apply closure_mono
      have : interior (A i) ⊆ interior (⋃ j, A j) := by
        apply interior_mono
        intro y hy
        exact Set.mem_iUnion.2 ⟨i, hy⟩
      exact this
    exact this
  exact hsubset hxInt
